title: Painted Lion Façade Mug
description:
Mug that features the front of the museum and Edward Kemeys’ Lions, 1893, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Sip your favorite beverage while gazing at an oil painting of the Lions which flank the Michigan Avenue entrance of the museum. 

  • Size: 11 ounces.
  • Dimensions: 3.75 in. tall 3.25 in. diameter.
  • Material: Ceramic.
  • Microwave safe.
